        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#12 · $0-249/MO · BEST FOR MARKETING WORKFLOWS</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Copy.ai — Best for marketing workflow automation beyond SEO</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For marketing teams that need AI writing for ads, emails, and social content — not primarily for SEO blog posts.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Copy.ai is a copywriting and workflow automation platform. Its 90+ templates cover promotional copy, email sequences, ad creative, and social posts — but it's not designed for SEO content. No SERP analysis, no NLP scoring, no rank tracking. The free plan includes 2,000 words monthly, making it a useful trial tool. It ranks #12 here because SEO optimization is genuinely secondary to its core purpose.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Free plan includes 2,000 words monthly — useful for evaluation</h4><p>Test the platform without committing. The free tier is genuinely functional for low-volume copywriting tasks.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>90+ templates for multi-channel marketing content</h4><p>Ad copy, email sequences, social captions, product descriptions — more template variety than any SEO-focused tool.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Workflow automation for multi-step content processes</h4><p>Chains content tasks together. Useful for teams with repeatable content production workflows across channels.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest limitation: no content optimization scoring, no SERP analysis, no auto-publishing</h4><p>Copy.ai is a copywriting tool that's been adapted for SEO use. If SEO content is your primary use case, start with a purpose-built SEO tool instead.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
        <p style="color: var(--text-3); font-size: 13px; margin-top: 8px;"><strong>Pricing:</strong> Free (2,000 words/mo) · Starter $36/mo per user · Advanced: custom</p>
      </div>
    </div>
